'''Khuliso Johnson Mudau''' also known as Sailorman (born 26 April 1995) is a South African professional [[Association football|soccer]] player who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right back]] for  [[South African Premier Division|Betway Premiership]] club [[Mamelodi Sundowns F.C.|Mamelodi Sundowns]] and the [[South Africa national soccer team|South Africa national team]].<ref>{{Soccerway|khuliso-johnson-mudau/460234|accessdate=9 October 2020}}</ref> He is regarded as one of the best Right Backs in the Betway Premiership.

==Early life==
He was born in [[Musina|Messina]]&nbsp;– now known as Musina&nbsp;– in [[Limpopo]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kickoff.com/news/articles/south-africa-news/categories/news/premiership/khuliso-mudau-defends-two-red-cards-row/597604|title=Khuliso Mudau defends himself after two red cards in a row|date=1 March 2019|website=Kick Off|accessdate=13 November 2020}}</ref>

==Club career==
After playing for [[JDR Stars F.C.|JDR Stars]], [[Magesi F.C.|Magesi]] and [[Black Leopards F.C.|Black Leopards]], he signed for [[Mamelodi Sundowns F.C.|Mamelodi Sundowns]] on a five-year contract in October 2020.<ref name="Sundowns announce Mudau capture and Mobbie's return">{{Cite web |date=9 October 2020 |title=Sundowns announce Mudau capture and Mobbie's return |url=https://global.fourfourtwo.com/sundowns-announce-mudau-capture-and-mobbies-return |access-date=9 October 2020 |website=[[FourFourTwo]] |language=en}}</ref>

He scored in the first goal in 3–0 win against Malian side [[Stade Malien]] in the 2025–26 CAF Champions League first leg quarterfinal.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Modiba |first=Katlego |date=2026-03-13 |title=Sundowns brush aside poor Stade Malien to move closer to semis |url=https://www.citizen.co.za/sport/soccer/sundowns-brush-aside-poor-stade-malien-to-move-closer-to-semis/ |access-date=2026-03-15 |website=The Citizen |language=en}}</ref>

Mudau was awarded the Outstanding Footballer of the Year in 2026 by the Icons of Africa Awards.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-03-10 |title=Mudau Earns 'Footballer Of The Year' Nod From Icons Of Africa |url=https://www.soccerladuma.co.za/psl/fan-park/khuliso-mudau-set-for-major-honour-at-icons-of-africa-awards |access-date=2026-03-15 |website=Soccer Laduma |language=en}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Mudau plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right back]].<ref name="Sundowns announce Mudau capture and Mobbie's return" /> He also specialises as a midfielder.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Zoutnet {{!}} Sport {{!}} Black Leopards away to collect more points|url=https://www.zoutnet.co.za/articles/sport/51392/2019-11-22/black-leopards-away-to-collect-more-points|access-date=2020-11-14|website=www.zoutnet.co.za}}</ref> Under the "shoe shine and the piano" system, he plays offensive as he frequently contributes to his teams attack through crosses placed in the box. He is praised for his ability to defend in 1 v 1 situations and he's all round defensive contributions , Summing up his style of play as Complete . Often hailed as one of the best right backs in Africa .

==International career==

On 1 December 2025, Mudau was called up to the South Africa squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/totalenergies-afcon-morocco-2025-fever-rises-as-broos-become-first-coach-to-unveil-final-squad/|title=TotalEnergies AFCON Morocco 2025 fever rises as Broos become first coach to unveil final squad|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=1 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

